<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-02-1304 </DOCNO><TEXT>The absorption of oral metronidazole in control rabbits and in rabbitsirradiated with cobalt-60 gamma radiation was studied. It was observedthat the bioavailability of metronidazole was significantly reduced inirradiated animals the reduction being dependent on the dose of radiation.The maximum decrease in absorption was seen 48h post-irradiation.</TEXT></DOC>